-- Asciano Opposes Coalminer, QR Gladstone Access Bid, Australian Reports
-- Nichola Saminather
-- 2010-07-27T21:40:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-27/asciano-opposes-coalminer-qr-gladstone-access-bid-australian-reports.html

          
          
             Asciano Group is opposing a bid by
16 Queensland coalminers to join with a unit of its competitor
QR National to use railway infrastructure associated with the
proposed Wiggins Island coal export terminal at Gladstone, the
Australian newspaper reported. The bid, which comes as a group
of coal companies seeks to buy QR Nationalâ€™s rail network, may
create competition issues, as some of the miners are members of
the takeover group, the newspaper said, citing Asciano Access
and Regulation Manager Stuart Ronan.  
